      <TR>
        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top' nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>Ryvinn</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>All bard soloing tricks take no mana, except charm kiting, so yes they have no down time, but it also takes a bard considerably longer to kill mobs than it does a necro.</P><P>In the case of bard fear kiting, they have to run with the mob as it is feared to do thier damage, the fear is AE so it is easy to get adds as you kite, even if you are fighting non agro mobs.  Also Bard songs only last 3 ticks and they can only twist 3 songs durring this time, that means either Snare, Fear and Haste -- the problem with this is when Snare is resisted the mob takes off at full speed and if Fear is resisted the bard takes a beating.  The option to avoid those problems is just twist 2 songs Fear and Snare this allows enough time to repeat a song should one get resisted.  Also remember Bard melee damage is fairly small so it takes a considerable amount of time to kill a mob in this manner.</P><P>Bards have other more efficient ways to solo mobs that are far less risky and more efficient than fear kitting, but I would still rate necro fear kitting as more efficient overall, when you consider we get mana regen spells.</P><P>Other Bard Solo tricks:<BR>Charm kiting - this is the most efficient while thier mana lasts.</P><P>Chant kiting - extreamly easy and safe, Sow/J-Boots + 3chants, run in circles, never get touched.  Bards can basically solo any outdoor, non-sommoning, non-caster, non-SoWed mob using this method, but it takes time, especially for mobs that are immune to one of thier chants.  For SoWed mobs or bards without JBoots or Sow potion, they can still use chant kitting, but have to replace 1 chant with Selos.  One of the great things about chant kitting is the songs also debuff, so once you get the chants to stick, it is easier to keep them on.</P><P>Reverse Chant kiting - same idea, but replace 1 chant with fear song to increase DoT damage, this works really well for bards who have drum of the beast or Epic, becasue they can also do weapon damage on top of chants.</P><P></P><P> </font></td>
